PHACTR4 (Phosphatase and Actin Regulator 4) is involved in the regulation of smooth muscle contraction and relaxation, which could affect gut motility and contribute to IBS symptoms.

TRNAU1AP (tRNA pseudouridine synthase 1 associated protein) is involved in the regulation of tRNA modification, which could affect gut function and inflammation. YTHDF2 (YTH domain containing 2) is involved in the regulation of gene expression and could potentially affect the gut-brain axis.

The other genes on the list are less directly related to IBS, but could still be involved in the underlying biology of the disorder.
